27/11/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn said Friday (25 November) that the pace of Stabilisation and Association Agreement (SAA) talks between BiH and the EU would depend on the Bosnian authorities and their readiness for co-operation and consensus. Rehn made this statement following a ceremony in Sarejevo, marking the official start of SAA negotiations. He voiced his confidence that the Bosnian leaders would be able to carry out crucial reforms. He also said completion of SAA talks was possible within one year, provided the requirements are met. (Fena, PBS BiH - 25/11/05)
